HEADWORD: Hippocrepian
<hw>Hip"po*crep"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Hippocrepiform</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of an order
of fresh-water Bryozoa, in which the tentacles are on a lophophore,
shaped like a horseshoe. See <er>Phylactol⟦ae⟧ma</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

